Download pfSense

1. Install VBOX v5
$ ./install-vbox.sh

2. Download the pfSense ISO

3. Run the create VBOX image script to create the bare iso
./create-pfSense-vbox.sh pfsense

VBoxManage startvm $vm --type headless

4. Login to the VBOX pfSense image (using remote desktop)

7. Setup VBox to start VMs automatically

http://askubuntu.com/questions/404665/how-to-start-virtual-box-machines-automatically-when-booting
